        "description": "Reads value from an INI file into a variable.\u003cbr\u003eNote: All parameters have to be enclosed within string delimiters. The VariableName has to be given without %..%.",
        "parameters": "\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSection\tTitle of the INI section to be read from\n\u003cbr\u003eKey\tKey to be read from\n\u003cbr\u003eDefaultvalue\tThe value to be given to the variable if the KEY does not exist\n\u003cbr\u003eFile\tFilename of the INIFILE to read from. If no path is specified, then the Windows user directory is assumed.\n\u003cbr\u003eVariableName\tThe name of the variable to which you want to assign the retrieved value\n\u003cbr\u003e/Script\tvariable is only valid during the execution of the script, from which the command gets executed. Best used, when the variable is only needed temporarely.\n\u003cbr\u003e/User\tWhen command is used in the UserAdd section and the user has no write access to the machine hive of the registry, this option must be used. Sets the variable in the user hive of the registry.\n\u003cbr\u003e/Machine \tVariable is set in the machine space. This is the default, when no parameter is specified.\n\u003cbr\u003e/Immediate\tNeeded, when a value gets read in the ServerAdd section and should be used in the same ServerAdd section. Cause variable to be set immediately instead of beeing written to the machvars.wms, where it would be available in the ClientAdd section\n\u003cbr\u003e/Volatile\t\tLoads the variables into the volatile environment, which will be deleted at next reboot. Best used for temporary variables in the ClientAdd or UserAdd section\n\u003cbr\u003e/NoErrors\tThis switch will ignore erros that might occur during reading the ini file.\n\u003cbr\u003e/NoFileSystemRedirection\n\u003cbr\u003e\t[TAB]On 64Bit operating system: do not turn off file system redirection (even if %_WindowsSystem64% is used)\n\u003cbr\u003e",
